			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Guild hall mana-regen works!!!<a name="73393"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 05 11:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>So, out of curriosity I drained off a bunch of my mana and headed to the guild hall.
<br />

<br />
My normal standing manaregen is 8 pts per tick.  I checked this for about 5 tics just to insure consistancy, then I stepped into the pool...
<br />

<br />
18 pts of mana regen per tic.
<br />

<br />
Not wanting to get my hopes up too high, I watched for a few tics and sure enough, it was still 18 every tic.  Then I stepped out of the pool and it returned to 8 pts.  I then repeated this little experiment 5 times.  Zoning twice.  The pool added 10 pts to my standing mana regen every time.
<br />

<br />
I don't know if it just adds a flat 10 pts to everybody's mana regen, or if it's based on your meditate skill, existing regen, level, class or a combination of all of them but the important thing is:
<br />

<br />
MANA POOLS WORK FOR BARD MANA REGEN!
<br />

<br />
WOOHA!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
