				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Guild hall mana-regen works!!!<a name="73481"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 20 05 12:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When I first started swarming I was 52 in PoN and I often ran out of mana, I had no FT items (or metnal clarity) at the time. I would do stalkers and work a spider or two or a tree into the kite to where all my pets would attack the same one mob that I can't charm, once that mob got low enough I would chant down. Doing this allowed me to kite doggies non stop: by the time I was low on doggies I would have more respawned for me to pick up. So once I was low on mana I would run to PoT to wait for mana. (at 2mp per tick it takes a loong while for mana to come back) My server - Modern Rasp, is unpopulated enough for me not to worry about losing my camp. I would have loved being able to go and regen my mana in the guild hall. So in other words I think this would be very useful for lower lvl swarming bards.
<br />
However now at 58 I have FT3 and one Mental Clarity for 5 mana per tick regen rate standing up. With these stats I was able to swarm  the nighstalkers in PoN for 3 hours non stop, and still had about half my mana left. So your point is well taken, the guild hall mana regen may not be so useful to us; but still it is nice to know that bards were not left out for once.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
